From 5e348bbd59f3fddc037d44d9bbc438286c945a72 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 19:50:45 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs prune` for safe run-dir cleanup
 (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add `flowai-workflow runs prune [--workflow <dir>] --keep <N> [--dry-run]`:
delete the oldest run directories under `<workflow>/runs/` so at most N
most-recent SAFE-to-delete runs remain. Status + start time come only from
replaying each run's journal; safety rules (all override --keep): never
delete a non-terminal run, never delete the run named by `runs/.lock`, and
treat a missing/unreplayable journal as unknown state (kept). Invalid
--keep is rejected with a clear error and non-zero exit; --dry-run is a
no-op that prints what would be deleted.

Selection/execution lives in src/state/prune.ts (reusing getRunDir, the
journal replayer, and the lock helpers — no duplicated path/replay logic);
cli.ts gains the `runs` dispatcher and help entry. Register FR-E83 in the
SRS and split the plugin-distribution FRs (E70/E71/E72) into a new
06b-plugin-distribution.md section to keep both files within the docs token
budget.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
