+# `runs prune` — safe cleanup of old run directories
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N>` subcommand that
+deletes the OLDEST run directories under `<workflow-dir>/runs/` so that at most
+`N` most-recent SAFE-to-delete runs remain, while never touching runs that are
+non-terminal, locked, or whose state cannot be determined. Run state is read
+exclusively by replaying each run's `journal.jsonl` with the existing replayer.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+- A run's only durable record is `runs/<run-id>/journal.jsonl` (append-only).
+  Status + start time come from replaying it via `replayRunJournal` /
+  `loadStateFromJournal` in `src/state/run-journal.ts`. No other state source
+  exists — a run dir without a replayable journal has unknown state.
+- Existing reusable `src/state/` helpers:
+  - `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` → `<workflowDir>/runs/<runId>` (path).
+  - `defaultLockPath(workflowDir)` → `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`;
+    `readLockInfo(lockPath)` → `{ run_id, pid, ... }`.
+  - `replayRunJournal(runDir)` → `{ state }`; `state.status` ∈
+    `running|completed|failed|aborted`; `state.started_at` ISO string.
+- Terminal statuses: `completed | failed | aborted`. `running` is non-terminal.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/cli.ts` dispatches `run | answer | init | mcp` subcommands via a
+  hand-rolled `switch`/positional parser; no `runs` group exists.
+- No module enumerates or classifies run directories; nothing deletes runs.
+- `--help` (`printUsage`) lists the four existing subcommands only.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Follow the existing argument-parsing style in `src/cli.ts`; no new deps.
+- Run-folder knowledge (run dir path, journal replay, lock location/format)
+  MUST reuse existing `src/state/` helpers — no duplicated path/replay logic.
+- `--keep` must be a non-negative integer; reject anything else with a clear
+  error and non-zero exit.
+- Safety (hard): never delete a non-terminal run; never delete the run named by
+  `runs/.lock`; missing/unreplayable journal ⇒ treated as non-terminal (keep)
+  and reported as skipped with reason.
+- `--dry-run` deletes nothing, prints what WOULD be deleted, exits 0.
+- Local filesystem only; no listing/inspection output beyond the summary; no
+  interactive prompts (flags only).
+- `deno task check` stays green; register requirement as FR-E83 in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`.
+
+### Keep-window semantics (resolved ambiguity)
+
+"At most N most-recent runs remain" is bounded by the safety rules (a
+non-terminal/locked/unreplayable run can never be deleted regardless of `--keep`).
+This plan resolves the tension conservatively ("when in doubt, keep"): the
+`--keep N` window is computed over the **eligible** set only — runs that are
+terminal, unlocked, and replayable — keeping the N newest of those and deleting
+the older eligible ones. Protected runs (non-terminal, locked, unreplayable)
+are always retained additionally and do NOT consume keep slots. This satisfies
+every required test (keeps N newest; `--keep 0` deletes all terminal unlocked;
+skips non-terminal/locked/unreplayable) and avoids the surprising deletion of a
+recent terminal run merely because a newer run is still in flight.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] (FR-E83) `selectRunsForPrune` keeps the N newest eligible runs and marks
+  older eligible runs for deletion. Test: `src/state/prune_test.ts::keeps N
+  newest, deletes older eligible`. Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) Non-terminal (`running`) runs are skipped with reason regardless
+  of `--keep`. Test: `src/state/prune_test.ts::skips non-terminal`. Evidence:
+  `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) The run named by `runs/.lock` is skipped with reason. Test:
+  `src/state/prune_test.ts::skips locked`. Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) Missing/unreplayable journal ⇒ skipped as non-terminal with
+  reason. Test: `src/state/prune_test.ts::missing/unreplayable journal kept`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) `--keep 0` deletes all terminal unlocked runs. Test:
+  `src/state/prune_test.ts::keep 0 deletes all terminal unlocked`. Evidence:
+  `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) `--dry-run` deletes nothing. Test:
+  `src/state/prune_test.ts::dry-run deletes nothing`. Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) Invalid `--keep` (negative / non-integer / missing) rejected with
+  clear error + non-zero exit. Test: `src/state/prune_test.ts::parseKeep rejects
+  invalid`. Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) `runs prune` appears in `--help`. Test:
+  `src/cli_test.ts::help lists runs prune` (or inline assert on `printUsage`).
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] (FR-E83) Summary prints deleted / kept / skipped counts with per-run skip
+  reason. Test: covered by `prune_test.ts` summary assertions. Evidence:
+  `deno task check`.
