+  (`documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`) with
+  `**Acceptance:**` field filled; register row in `documents/index.md`.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Files
+
+- NEW `src/state/prune.ts` — selection policy + execution + arg parsing.
+- NEW `src/state/prune_test.ts` — unit tests on temp-dir fixtures.
+- EDIT `src/cli.ts` — `runs` subcommand dispatch + `--help` entry.
+- EDIT `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md` —
+  FR-E83 section.
+- EDIT `documents/requirements-engine.md` (index FR map) + `documents/index.md`.
+
+### `src/state/prune.ts`
+
+- `parseKeep(raw: string | undefined): number` — require a non-negative integer
+  string; throw `Error("Invalid --keep value: ... Expected a non-negative
+  integer.")` otherwise. (Mirrors the `--budget` / `--cycles` validators in
+  `cli.ts`.)
+- `interface PrunePlan { toDelete: PrunedRun[]; toKeep: PrunedRun[];
+  skipped: SkippedRun[] }` where `PrunedRun = { runId; runDir; startedAt }` and
+  `SkippedRun = { runId; runDir; reason }`.
+- `async selectRunsForPrune(workflowDir, keep): Promise<PrunePlan>`:
+  1. `runsDir = dirname(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))` (reuse lock helper for
+     the `runs/` root — no `/runs` literal duplication).
+  2. `lockedRunId` = `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir)).run_id`,
+     swallowing NotFound/parse errors (no lock ⇒ none protected).
+  3. Enumerate directory entries under `runsDir` (skip files like `.lock`).
+     If `runsDir` itself is missing ⇒ empty plan.
+  4. For each `runId` (entry name), `runDir = getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)`:
+     - `runId === lockedRunId` ⇒ skipped, reason `"locked by runs/.lock"`.
+     - else `try { state = (await replayRunJournal(runDir)).state }` —
+       on throw ⇒ skipped, reason `"journal missing or unreplayable — unknown
+       state (kept)"`.
+     - else if `state.status` not in `{completed,failed,aborted}` ⇒ skipped,
+       reason `"status '<status>' not terminal"`.
+     - else eligible `{ runId, runDir, startedAt: state.started_at }`.
+  5. Sort eligible by `startedAt` descending (tie-break `runId` desc for
+     determinism). `toKeep = eligible.slice(0, keep)`; `toDelete =
+     eligible.slice(keep)`.
+- `interface PruneSummary { deleted; kept; skipped; plan }`.
+- `async executePrune(workflowDir, keep, dryRun): Promise<PruneSummary>` —
+  builds plan; when `!dryRun`, `Deno.remove(runDir, { recursive: true })` for
+  each `toDelete`; returns counts + plan.
+- `formatPruneSummary(summary, dryRun): string` — human summary lines:
+  header (`Dry run — nothing deleted.` when dryRun), `Deleted: K`, `Kept: K`,
+  `Skipped: K`, then one line per skipped run `- <runId>: <reason>` and per
+  deleted run `- <runId>` (would-delete under dry-run).
+
+### `src/cli.ts`
+
+- Add `parsePruneArgs(args): { workflowDir?: string; keepRaw?: string;
+  dryRun: boolean }` near `parseAnswerArgs` (accept `--workflow`/`--workflow=`,
+  `--keep`/`--keep=`, `--dry-run`).
